01:31:58.420 --> 01:32:00.421
to share our creative vision.

01:32:00.505 --> 01:32:01.797
Nothing was impossible

01:32:01.882 --> 01:32:04.216
for John and Maxine
in the early days.

01:32:04.301 --> 01:32:06.135
Their union was a joyous one,

01:32:06.219 --> 01:32:07.887
and together
they worked tirelessly

01:32:07.971 --> 01:32:10.389
to further Malkovich's
puppeteering career.

01:32:10.474 --> 01:32:15.102
John Malkovich, the artist,
and Maxine, the entrepreneur,

01:32:15.187 --> 01:32:17.229
they make this character,

01:32:17.314 --> 01:32:21.025
this protean figure
that we call John Malkovich.

01:32:21.109 --> 01:32:25.237
But some say Maxine has changed
since becoming pregnant,

01:32:25.322 --> 01:32:28.616
recoiling from the limelight
and, rumor has it,

01:32:28.992 --> 01:32:31.452
from her husband's affections.

01:32:39.377 --> 01:32:41.629
I'm so sorry.

01:32:46.968 --> 01:32:49.512
Malkovich shows us

01:32:50.013 --> 01:32:53.349
a reflection of ourselves,
our frailties

01:32:53.558 --> 01:32:56.644
and our, you know,

01:32:56.728 --> 01:32:58.854
desperate humanity.

01:32:59.439 --> 01:33:03.567
That's what makes him one of the
most relevant artists of our time.

01:33:04.277 --> 01:33:07.947
And what does the future
hold for John Horatio Malkovich?

01:33:08.031 --> 01:33:12.451
Well, to quote the Bard, "He's
got the world on a string."

01:33:12.536 --> 01:33:14.161
As the poet said,

01:33:14.246 --> 01:33:17.790
"The puppeteer's voice need not
merely be the record of man.

01:33:17.874 --> 01:33:20.167
"It can be one of the pillars,
the props,

01:33:20.252 --> 01:33:22.503
"to help him endure
and prevail."

01:33:22.587 --> 01:33:24.547
And I believe that.

01:33:24.965 --> 01:33:26.382
